{{Headerbox|header=<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #344469, 1px -1px 0 #344469, -1px 1px 0 #353469, -1px -1px 0 #353469, 1px 0px 0 #FFFFFF, 0px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px 0px 0 #FFFFFF, 0px -1px 0 #FFFFFF"; "position: relative; top: 20px;">'''"The windows to the soul do look both ways."'''</span>|file=inhindsight.png|speed=8s}}
<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">{{Class|p1=3|p2=4|p3=2|level=5.55|top-color=d|p1-color=d|p2-color=d|p3-color=d}}


<font size="5px">'''//''DESCRIPTION'' //'''</font>{{Simple Image Block|image=LookBothWays_3.png|caption=A close-up of Level 5.55's concrete structures, displaying both minor graffiti and wretched watchers}}

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Level 5.55 is a sub-level between [[Level 5]] and [[Level 6]]. It appears as a mid-sized warehouse with conjoined rooms made up of temporary walls measuring roughly 20 square feet in each direction. These walls are weak enough to be broken with one's own hands, revealing a 2-foot gap before another wall made of metal cladding in further reaches of Level 5.55. Most rooms in Level 5.55 contain concrete monoliths, barriers and graffiti; and an air conditioning unit can be heard with no discernible source. Level 5.55 is dotted with many "safe rooms," dark with shrink-wrapped floors and dim spotlights trailing behind clusters of small pillars called "pillar crawlers," that slide very slowly across the room. Level 5.55 is also subject to [[Phenomenon 15]], forcing wanderers apart; making colonies impossible to construct.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Porcelain eyes outlined with black spray paint are found on every concrete structure in the level, accompanied by random graffiti. The eyes give wanderers a deep sense of paranoia, and a feeling of being watched when in direct sight of them. This is due to the eyes emitting an excessive amount of psychic energy, contributing significantly to the development of [[Phenomenon 35|Roth syndrome]], lending the name, "wretched watchers." {{Simple Image Block|image=LookBothWays_1.png|caption=An alternate angle of Level 5.55's sculptures with multiple wretched watchers visible.|align=right|captioncellstyle=color: white|imagecellstyle=color: black|style=color: black}}
<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">When entering Level 5.55, it is advised to quickly and calmly enter a dark room to avoid the gaze of wretched watchers before one can get their bearings. Under no circumstances should one perform any action that may create large amounts of sound, such as dropping a heavy item, throwing objects, breaking a wall, and/or shouting. Any loud noise will trigger a period where the level falls silent, and all wretched watchers in the vicinity begin staring at the wanderer who caused it. The combined gaze of five wretched watchers has been reported to paralyze wanderers in fear and severely degrade one's mental state.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;"><font size= 5px>'''//''ENTITIES'' //'''</font>

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">'''Wretched Watchers -'''

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Despite being near-inanimate objects, wretched watchers still display a low level of awareness that classifies them as entities as evident by their production of psychic energy and their staring behavior. They are native solely to Level 5.55, and are found built into concrete structures of varying size and shape. Wretched watchers are made up of porcelain, glass lenses, and black spray paint that coats the surrounding surface in a black outline.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Though the glass lens of a Wretched watcher's pupil commonly reflects light as expected, rarely, the reflection shown in the glass lens of each Wretched Watcher will show a unique scene of either the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]] or Backrooms, though it is unknown to whom these visions are tailored.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Any organism caught in the gaze of a wretched watcher will experience symptoms of heightened paranoia and a fight-or-flight response. These symptoms compound when under the gaze of multiple Wretched Watchers. Wretched watchers become animated whenever an excess amount of sound is produced, staring directly at either the wanderer that produced the sound or the closest living thing, causing extreme distress and fear in the subject, often causing said subject to freeze up when under the gaze of multiple wretched watchers.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Many of the negative effects wretched watchers have on the mental state of wanderers are attributed to their unique ability to channel psychic energy. This allows them to pour large amounts of psychic energy into the target of their gaze, transferring negative emotions, and compromising mental stability. These effects create the perfect conditions for the acceleration and initiation of [[Phenomenon 35|Roth syndrome]].

[[File:Wretched stalker.gif|thumb|355x355px]]
<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">'''Wretched Stalker -'''

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">The Wretched Stalker is a lanky, bipedal figure that has an appearance that blends in with the concrete structures in Level 5.55, with one porcelain eye that is identical to a wretched watcher. The Wretched Stalker is intangible and passes through walls, leading to speculation on whether it is an entity or hallucination, but due to its appearance never changing from various accounts, it has been deemed a unique entity.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">The Wretched Stalker has never been recorded harming any wanderers directly, but it has been known to poke its head out through walls, appear from around corners, and stalk wanderers in a predatory manner. It is important to maintain composure during encounters with it and keep its presence in mind, as it is easy to accidentally yell or shout on instinct when the Wretched Stalker appears suddenly.</span>


<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;"><font size= 5px>'''//''COLONIES & OUTPOSTS'' //'''</font>

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Due to [[Phenomenon 15]], no physical colonies can be established.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">There have been cases of groups communicating with each other through radio; however, how these signals travel to one another is still unknown. Whispers can be picked up within close proximity of Wretched Watchers on certain frequencies, but these whispers are nearly inaudible, making it impossible to decipher.


<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;"><font size= 5px>'''//''ENTRANCES & EXITS'' //'''</font>

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">ENTRANCES:

# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Doors labelled with an eye on hotel-centered levels, especially [[Level 5]] or any of its sub-levels, will open to Level 5.55 and disappear when entered.
# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Wandering through [[Level 6]] can randomly transport you to one of Level 5.55's dark rooms.
# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Entering warehouses in [[Level 32]] can lead here.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">EXITS:

# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Doors labelled with an eye can be found in Level 5.55 and will send wanderers to any hotel-centred level, or back to the level they came from, granted that they entered through one of the doors.
# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Numbered doors in Level 5.55 open to [[Level 21]].
# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Breaking through the metal cladding on far reaches of Level 5.55 will lead to [[Level Phi]].
# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Breaking or vaulting over a temporary wall has a chance of landing one in [[Level 20]].
# <span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Losing consciousness can cause a [[No-Clipping|no-clip]] to a random level, usually within the [[Level List#Main Nine|Main Nine]].</span>
# <span style="background:linear-gradient(to right, #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF, #000000); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;">Breaking through the near-indestructible floor will cause a slow transition into [[The Void]].</span>
<div style="text-align:center">





<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">I can feel them watching me.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">I can feel my emotions draining from my body.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">I can feel them breathing down my neck.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Those things... are alive.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">They call to me.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Speak to me.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Beg for me to help them.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">At the peak of my delusions, the floor opened up and swallowed me whole.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">I fell.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">I don't know how long- or how far.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">But eventually... I was one of them.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Please, run away.

<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">Don't end up like me.


<span style="color: #FFFFFF !important;">I'll be watching, {{USERNAME}}
